{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia|title', 'text' : 'The Lamentations.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia100|title', 'text' : 'First Section.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia100|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 1.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia101|text', 'text' : 'In the tomb they laid you, * you, O Christ, who are Life; * in amazement angel armies lift up their song * as they glorify your self-abasement, Lord.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia102|text', 'text' : 'Life, how can you perish, * or how dwell in a tomb? * Yet the royal hall of Death you now bring to nought, * and from Hades' realm you raise the dead again.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia103|text', 'text' : 'Now we magnify you, * O Lord Jesus, our King, * we pay honor to your Passion and burial * for from foul corruption you saved us thru them.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia104|text', 'text' : 'King of all, O Jesus, * who established earth's bounds * on this day you make your home in a little tomb, * raising up the dead of ages from their graves.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia105|text', 'text' : 'O my Christ, my Jesus, * King and Monarch of all, * seeking what have you descended to those in Hell? * Was it not to liberate the mortal race?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia106|text', 'text' : 'He who governs all things * here is seen as a corpse, * new the grave in which his body is laid to rest, * he the one who empties graves of all their dead.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia107|text', 'text' : 'In the tomb they laid you, * you, O Christ who are Life; * death itself you brought to nothing by your own death, * and became the fount of life for all the world.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia108|text', 'text' : 'Guilty with the guilty * you were judged, O my Christ, * at the moment you wrought justice for all of us, * from the ancient trickster's foul and evil deeds.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia109|text', 'text' : 'Fairer he in beauty * than are all mortal kind, * now a corpse we see, unsightly, bereft of form, * he who beautified the nature of all things.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia110|text', 'text' : 'How could Hell endure it, * when in splendor you came, * and how not be swiftly shattered and plunged in dark, * blinded by the blazing glory of your light?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia111|text', 'text' : 'Light that saves, O Jesus, * you are sweetness to me, * in the darkness of the grave how can you lie hid? * O forbearance that no language can express!'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia112|text', 'text' : 'Angels are bewildered, * and the bodiless host * at a loss, O Christ, before that great mystery * your ineffable entombment, beyond speech.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia113|text', 'text' : 'O most strange of wonders! * What new deeds we now see! * He who gave me my life's breath, lies unbreathing now, * borne to burial at noble Joseph's hands.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia114|text', 'text' : 'Like the sun when setting, * to the tomb you descend, * yet, O Christ, your Father's bosom you do not leave. * What strange paradox, what wondrous thing this is.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia115|text', 'text' : 'As the sky's true monarch, * as true king of the earth, * though enclosed within the narrowest sepulcher, * you were known by all creation, Jesus Lord.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia116|text', 'text' : 'In the tomb they laid you, * Christ the maker of all; * then were Hell's foundations shaken; they tremble now, * as the graves of mortal kind are opened wide.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia117|text', 'text' : 'He who in the hollow * of his hand holds the earth, * in the flesh is put to death and lies in earth's grasp, * as he now redeems the dead from Hades' grip.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia118|text', 'text' : 'You rose from corruption, * O my Savior, my life, * having died and gone to dwell there among the dead, * smashed and shattered Hades' brazen bolts and bars.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia119|text', 'text' : 'Like a burning lampstand * here the flesh of our God, * as beneath a bushel measure, now lies concealed * under earth and puts the gloom of Hell to flight.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia120|text', 'text' : 'Nothing can contain you, * yet the Heavenly hosts, * with the noble Joseph and with Nicodemus now * hasten to enclose you in a little grave.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia121|text', 'text' : 'Willingly, my Jesus, * slain and laid underground, * fount of life, you gave me life when I lay in death, * when by bitterest transgressions I was slain.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia122|text', 'text' : 'By your Passion, Jesus, * all creation was changed, * all things suffered with you, Word, knowing you to be * the Maintainer and Sustainer of the world.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia123|text', 'text' : 'Death who eats up all things * swallowed you, Rock of Life; * when you entered in his belly he vomited, * spewing forth the dead gulped down from every age.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia124|text', 'text' : 'There, O Christ, they laid you, * in a newly made grave, * and the nature of us mortals you then renewed, * when from death you rose in majesty divine.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia125|text', 'text' : 'Down to earth, O Master, * to save Adam you came, * and not finding him on earth, you descended, Lord, * to the depths of Hades, searching for him there.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia126|text', 'text' : 'All the earth was shaken * and it trembled in fear, * and the light-bearer, O Word, hid its rays away * to see you, the greatest Light, hid in the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia127|text', 'text' : 'Willingly as mortal, * O my Savior, you die, * but as God you raised the dead back to life again, * from their graves and the abysmal depths of sin.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia128|text', 'text' : 'Tears of lamentation * she pours out over you, * as your mother the pure Virgin, O Jesus, cries, * "How my son am I to lay you in the tomb?"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia129|text', 'text' : 'Like a wheat grain buried * in the bosom of Earth, * you have yielded harvest in great abundance, Lord, * raising up all Adam's mortal progeny.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia130|text', 'text' : 'Now you have been hidden * like the sun 'neath the earth * and been covered over, veiled by the night of death. * Dawn again, O Savior, dawn more brightly yet.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia131|text', 'text' : 'As the moon eclipses * the sun's disk, Savior Lord, * now the sepulcher has hidden you from our eyes, * in the flesh you undergo eclipse by death.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia132|text', 'text' : 'Life itself, Christ Savior, * having tasted of death, * freed all mortal kind from death, liberated us * and the gift of life he now bestows on all.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia133|text', 'text' : 'By your death, O Savior, * you lead back into life * Adam, who of old by envy was brought to death, * as in flesh as a new Adam you appear.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia134|text', 'text' : 'The angelic orders * were amazed to behold * you, our Savior, for our sake laid out as a corpse; * with their wings they veil their faces from the sight.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia135|text', 'text' : 'Noble Joseph takes you * as a corpse from the Tree; * new the grave, O Word, in which he now buries you. * But as God arise and save all human kind!'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia136|text', 'text' : 'To the angels, Savior, * you are gladness and joy, * but a cause of grief you now have become to them, * as they see you in the flesh a lifeless corpse.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia137|text', 'text' : 'Lord you lift up with you, * lifted up on the Tree, * every living mortal, but now laid under earth * all who lie beneath it you raise up again.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia138|text', 'text' : 'In the flesh, O Savior, * like a lion you slept; * as a lion cub he rises, our Mighty Dead, * sloughing off the flesh's feebleness and age.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia139|text', 'text' : 'Mother Eve you fashioned * from a rib, which you took * from the side of Adam; Lord, now your side is pierced, * and from thence there gush forth purifying streams.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia140|text', 'text' : 'Sacrificed in secret * was the lamb slain of old; * under open skies, O Savior longsuffering, * cleansing all creation, you were sacrificed.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia141|text', 'text' : 'Who is there can tell it, * this dread thing, truly new: * see, the Master of creation today accepts * death and suffering, and dies now for our sake.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia142|text', 'text' : '"How can life's Dispenser * now be seen as a corpse?" * cried the Angels in amazement. "How can our God * be confined here, be shut up within a grave?"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia143|text', 'text' : 'When the lance, O Savior, * pierced your side, you let fall * drops of life on Eve, who from life had banished me, * giving life to her you gave me life as well.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia144|text', 'text' : 'Mortal kind you gathered * into one, Jesus Lord, * when stretched out upon the Tree, and your side was pierced; * from that life-source you pour pardon forth for all.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia145|text', 'text' : 'Noble Joseph, Savior, * filled with dread lays you out, * nobly readies you and buries you as a corpse, * trembling awestruck at the sight of your dread form.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia146|text', 'text' : 'Willingly as mortal, * you went down 'neath the earth; * from the earth's depths you lead back up to Heaven's height * all of those, O Jesus, who lay fallen there.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia147|text', 'text' : 'Though a corpse we see you, * yet alive as our God * you gave life again to mortals who once were slain, * put to death the one who brought me to my death.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia148|text', 'text' : 'O the joy the gladness, * O the boundless delight, * with which, Jesus, you filled those who lay bound in Hell, * when you made light blaze throughout its murky depths.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia149|text', 'text' : 'Lord, your pains I worship, * and your burial praise, * and I magnify your might, Lover of mankind. * By them I am freed from passions which destroy.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia150|text', 'text' : 'A great sword was sharpened * against you, O my Christ, * but the strong one's mighty sword has been blunted now, * and the sword that guarded Eden is turned back.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia151|text', 'text' : 'When the Ewe that bore him * saw the Lamb that was slain, * shot with anguish she lamented and cried aloud, * rousing all the flock to join its cry to hers.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia152|text', 'text' : 'Buried in a tomb, Lord, * and descended to Hell, * yet, O Savior, you have emptied the sepulchers, * mighty Hades you stripped naked, O my Christ.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia153|text', 'text' : 'Willingly, O Savior, * you went down 'neath the earth, * granted life again to mortals whom death had slain, * in the glory of the Father led them up.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia154|text', 'text' : 'Shameful death he suffered * in the flesh for our sake, * who is one of the divine holy Trinity. * Quails the sun and all earth shudders at the sight.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia155|text', 'text' : 'From the tribe of Judah * from that bitterest source, * came the offspring who cast Jesus into the pit, * him who furnished them with manna for their food.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia156|text', 'text' : 'Judge he stands for judgment * before Pilate as judge, * and the unjust judge condemns him to unjust death, * to be put to death upon that Tree, the Cross.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia157|text', 'text' : 'Why so boastful Israel, * people tainted with blood? * Why did you deliver Barabbas from his pains, * yet hand over Christ the Savior to a Cross?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia158|text', 'text' : 'With your hand you fashioned * Adam out of the earth; * for him you became by nature a man, O Lord, * and were crucified for him by your own will.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia159|text', 'text' : 'You obeyed your Father * and descended, O Word, * to the depth of dreadful Hell, to the realm of Death, * and raised up again the race of mortal kind.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia160|text', 'text' : 'Bitterly lamenting, * "Woe is me, O my light! * my heart's longing and the Light of the World, alas! * Woe is me, my heart's desire," the Virgin cried.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia161|text', 'text' : 'Murderous, malicious, * men whose deeds for vengeance cry! * See the grave-clothes and the napkin left lying here, * as Christ rises from the dead: are you not shamed?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia162|text', 'text' : 'Murdering disciple, * bloodstained man, show me now * all the manner, all the ways of your wickedness, * thru which you became betrayer of our Christ.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia163|text', 'text' : 'Monster of destruction, * blind, implacable fool! * How can you pretend to act from philanthropy, * when you sold the Myrrh for thirty silver pence?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia164|text', 'text' : 'How much did they pay you * for the heavenly Myrrh? * What did you receive as price of the precious One? * You found raving madness, Satan, most accursed.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia165|text', 'text' : 'If you suffered anguish * as a friend of the poor, * when for mercy on a soul precious myrrh was poured, * how, then, can you sell the fount of light for gold?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia166|text', 'text' : '"O God's Word, my gladness, * O my Lord and my God, * how can I endure your burial for three days? * As a mother now my heart is torn with grief."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia167|text', 'text' : '"Who will give me water, * give me fountains of tears," * cried the Virgin bride of God, "that I may lament * and may weep for my sweet Jesus, who lies slain?"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia168|text', 'text' : '"Mountain heights and valleys, * all the whole human race, * come, all creatures, come lament and shed tears with me, * weep with me, who am the Mother of your God."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia169|text', 'text' : '"Savior, light eternal, * the delight of my heart, * when shall I see you, my gladness, my only joy?" * cried the Virgin most afflicted in her grief.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia170|text', 'text' : 'Like a rock, O Savior, * sharp and flinty and hard, * you received the blow, but poured forth as source of life, * streams of living water, bringing life to all.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia171|text', 'text' : 'As if from one fountain * as from only one spring, * from the double stream that flows from your side we drink, * and we pluck the fruit that grants immortal life.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia172|text', 'text' : 'By your will we see you, * as a corpse in the tomb, * but you live, O Word and Savior, as you foretold, * by your Resurrection you raise mortal kind.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia1TrVerse|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia1Tr|text', 'text' : 'Word, we sing your praises, * as the Lord God of all, * with the Father and your most Holy Spirit, Lord, * and we glorify your burial divine.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia1TVerse|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia1T|text', 'text' : 'Now we call you blessed, * All-Pure Mother of God, * and in faith we hold in honor and venerate * the three day entombment of your Son our God.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia1F|text', 'text' : 'In the tomb they laid you, * you, O Christ, who are Life; * in amazement angel armies lift up their song * as they glorify your self-abasement, Lord.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia200|title', 'text' : 'Second Section.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia200|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 1.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia201|text', 'text' : 'It is right indeed * we should magnify the one who grants life, * you, that stretched your hands wide upon the Cross, * broke and smashed the might and power of the foe.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia202|text', 'text' : 'It is right indeed * you to magnify, who fashion all things, * your pains from corruption deliver us, * and your Passion grants dispassion to our souls.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia203|text', 'text' : 'All Earth quaked in fear * and the sun concealed itself, O Savior, * when, O Christ, our light, you set bodily, * as the light that knows no evening was entombed.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia204|text', 'text' : 'Sleeping in the tomb * with the sleep that breathes forth life, Anointed, * from sin's heavy sleep you, as God, aroused * all the human race that sin had held enthralled.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia205|text', 'text' : '"Of all woman-kind * I alone bore you, my child, without pain; * cruel pangs now wrack me as I behold * your great suffering", the Holy Virgin cries.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia206|text', 'text' : 'Seeing you on high, * never separated from the Father, * yet below on Earth, laid out as a corpse, * the dread Seraphim, my Saviour, shake with fear.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia207|text', 'text' : 'See, the Temple Veil, * rent asunder at your crucifixion, * Heaven's beacons hide, O my Christ, their light, * to see you, the Sun, now hid beneath the earth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia208|text', 'text' : 'He who at the start * by His will alone set Earth revolving, * lifeless as a mortal sets under earth; * let the sky now shake and tremble at the sight.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia209|text', 'text' : 'Human-kind you formed, * with your own hand fashioned us, O Saviour, * now, O Sun, you set underneath the earth, * raising companies of mortals from the fall.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia210|text', 'text' : 'Come, now, let us sing, * let our sacred hymn lament the dead Christ, * singing as the Myrrh-bearing women did, * that with them we too may hear the word "rejoice!"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia211|text', 'text' : 'Truly you are Myrrh, * truly, Word of God, the Myrrh Unfailing, * so it was myrrh-bearers brought myrrh to you, * to the Living God brought myrrh as to the dead.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia212|text', 'text' : 'Buried, O my Christ, * the great palaces of Hell you shattered, * Death you put to death by your death, O Lord, * from corruption you set free those born of earth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia213|text', 'text' : 'To the grave descends * he, the Wisdom of our God, that pours out * streams of life; descending into a tomb, * giving life to those in Hades deepest depths.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia214|text', 'text' : '"Willingly by death * I was wounded in the flesh, dear Mother, * thus the broken nature of mortal kind * to renew, so do not beat your breast in grief."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia215|text', 'text' : 'When beneath the Earth * you had set, the Morning Star of justice, * you aroused the dead as if they but slept, * as you put to flight the murk and gloom of Hell.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia216|text', 'text' : 'Sown with tears today, * the life-breathing grain of two-fold nature, * here within earth's furrows the grain is sown, * but tomorrow it will burst once more to life.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia217|text', 'text' : 'Trembling, Adam quailed, * when God walked in Paradise, he feared him, * but rejoices now as God enters Hell. * As of old he fell, so now he rises up.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia218|text', 'text' : 'Offerings of tears, * O my Christ, your Mother poured out, weeping, * as in flesh you lay buried in the grave, * "But arise, my Son, as you foretold", she cried.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia219|text', 'text' : 'Filled with godly fear, * in a new tomb noble Joseph hides you, * singing, Saviour, hymns for your burial, * hymns befitting God and mingled with laments.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia220|text', 'text' : 'Bolts of bitter grief * pierced you Mother's soul, and nails of anguish, * when she saw you nailed to a Tree, O Word, * saw you fastened to the Cross with cruel nails.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia221|text', 'text' : 'When her eyes beheld * you who are the whole world's sweetness, * drinking, O my Saviour, the bitter drink, * your sweet Mother drenched her eyes with bitter tears.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia222|text', 'text' : '"Dreadful is the wound, * all my inward parts are rent asunder, * as your unjust slaughter I see, O Word", * cried the Virgin most afflicted as she wept.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia223|text', 'text' : '"Tell me, Word of God, * how am I to close you lips and sweet eyes, * how to bury you as befits the dead?" * cried the noble Joseph, shivering with fear.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia224|text', 'text' : 'Sacred hymns they sing, * Nicodemus and the noble Joseph, * while the Seraphim join them in their hymn * for the burial of Christ, who now lies dead.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia225|text', 'text' : 'Sun of justice, now * you have set beneath the earth, my Saviour, * Therefore she, the Moon that gave birth to you, * is eclipsed with grief, at seeing you no more.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia226|text', 'text' : 'Hades trembled then, * when he saw you, the Life-giving Saviour, * in your might despoiling him of his wealth, * raising up the dead he held from every age.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia227|text', 'text' : 'Once the night has passed * then again, O Word, the bright Sun blazes; * radiant you blaze forth, when after death, * as though from a bridal chamber, you arise.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia228|text', 'text' : 'How Earth quaked with fear, * O Creator, as into her bosom, * shaking, she received you, my Saving Lord, * by her fearful shaking she awoke the dead.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia229|text', 'text' : 'With sweet myrrh, O Christ, * Nicodemus and the noble Joseph * laid you out for burial strange and new, * as they cried aloud, "Now tremble, all the earth!"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia230|text', 'text' : 'Maker of the light, * you have set, and with you sets the sunlight; * all creation, trembling and shuddering, * now proclaims you as the Maker all things.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia231|text', 'text' : 'Christ, our Cornerstone, * Him a stone hewn from the rock now covers; * Tremble Earth to see how a mortal man * hides away our God as mortal in a tomb!'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia232|text', 'text' : '"O my Child, behold * the disciple whom you loved; my sweet one, * see your Mother too, and grant us a word", * cried the Virgin as she raised her sad lament.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia233|text', 'text' : 'O, Life-giving Word, * even stretched out on the Cross and nailed there, * you, as Lord of Life, did not kill the Jews, * granting resurrection even to their dead.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia234|text', 'text' : 'Suffering, O Word, * you were quite bereft of form and beauty; * Rising, Lord, you shone forth resplendently, * and with your Godhead's rays made mortals fair.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia235|text', 'text' : 'In the flesh you set, * 'neath the earth, Dawn Star that knows no evening, * at height of noon-day the sun grew dark, * as unable to endure the fearful sight.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia236|text', 'text' : 'Sun and moon grew dark, * they are images of faithful servants, * who, as mourners, Saviour, attire themselves * in the sombre mourners' robes of deepest black.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia237|text', 'text' : '"Though you hung there dead, * the centurion knew you as true God. * See, with fear I shake", noble Joseph cried, * "Tell me, how am I to touch you with my hands?"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia238|text', 'text' : 'Adam lay asleep, * and, while sleeping, from his side brought forth death. * You, O Word of God, who are sleeping here, * now are pouring from your side life for the world.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia239|text', 'text' : 'For a while you slept, * to the dead who lay in Hell you brought life. * Rising up, O Good One, you then raised up * all the multitudes of dead from every age.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia240|text', 'text' : 'Vine from which life flows! * As above the earth, Lord, you were lifted, * you poured forth the wine of salvation then, * now I glorify your Passion and your Cross.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia241|text', 'text' : 'Lords of Angel Hosts, * when they saw you, O my Saviour, naked, * blood-stained, and condemned, how did they endure * to perceive your crucifiers' insolence?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia242|text', 'text' : 'What perversity! * Come, most crooked race of Hebrews, tell us, * how could you condemn the Anointed One, * when you knew the temple would be raised again.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia243|text', 'text' : 'In a mocking cloak * you have clothed the one who orders all things. * He arrayed the Earth, and most wondrously, * he it was who strewed the stars across the skies.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia244|text', 'text' : 'Like the pelican, * you gave life, O Word, to your dead children, * wounded in your side, you let life-blood flow, * letting fall life-giving drops of blood on all.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia245|text', 'text' : 'Jesus stayed the sun, * as of old he smote the foreign foe, Lord; * you, Christ, hid its light as you overthrew * that great prince, the Lord of darkness and of death.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia246|text', 'text' : 'O Compassionate, * while remaining in your Father's bosom, * mortal nature willingly you assumed, * and as mortal man, O Christ, went down to Hell.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia247|text', 'text' : 'He who hung the earth * on the waters, on a Cross is lifted, * as a lifeless corpse he is laid in earth, * which, unable to endure it, dreads and quakes.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia248|text', 'text' : '"Woe is me, my Son! * For I hoped as king to see you reigning, * whom I see condemned, hanging on the Cross," * the pure Virgin Mother voices her lament .'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia249|text', 'text' : '"Gabriel announced, * in the wondrous message that he brought me, * the eternal kingdom he said would be * the possession of my Jesus, my dear Son".'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia250|text', 'text' : '"Woe, alas for me! * Now a prophecy has found fulfilment, * As the just man Symeon had foretold, * now, Emmanuel, your sword has pierced my heart."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia251|text', 'text' : 'Are you not ashamed? * Tell me, do not all those dead he raised up * shame you, for the Giver of life is he, * whom from spiteful envy, Jews, you did to death .'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia252|text', 'text' : 'Bitterly she wept, * your all-blameless Mother, when she saw you * lying dead, O Word, lying in the tomb, * the eternal God no language can express.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia253|text', 'text' : 'Seeing you, my Christ, * you, the Light invisible, now hidden, * lifeless in the grave, then the sun on high * shook and trembled as its light grew dark in fear.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia254|text', 'text' : 'When she saw your death * then your Mother free from all defilement * cried out, O my Christ, bitterly to you, * "Life, I beg, do not delay among the dead!"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia255|text', 'text' : 'Hades, death's dread lord, * shook in fear, he shuddered when he saw you, * Sun of glory, deathless and radiant, * and he gave up all his prisoners in haste.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia256|text', 'text' : 'Terrible indeed, * great the sight that now is seen, O Saviour, * He, the cause of life, willing went to death, * wishing life to bring as gift to all mankind.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia257|text', 'text' : 'Lord, your side was pierced, * nails were hammered through your hands, O Saviour, * from your side came healing to heal the wound, * and to cure the greed of our first parents' hands.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia258|text', 'text' : 'Once for Rachel's son * house by house were all set sadly weeping. * With his Mother now, the Disciples' choir * in its grief mourns and laments the Virgin's Son.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia259|text', 'text' : 'With their hands they gave * a great blow upon the cheek of Jesus, * Christ, who with his hand fashioned all mankind * Christ, who with his hand has crushed the Beast's foul fangs.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia260|text', 'text' : 'With our hymns, O Christ, * all the faithful bring their adoration, * to your crucifixion and burial; * by your burial we have been freed from death.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia2TrVerse|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia2Tr|text', 'text' : 'Great eternal God, * co-eternal Word and Holy Spirit, * look down in your goodness on those who rule, * grant their sceptres strength against the warlike foe.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia2TVerse|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia2T|text', 'text' : 'Wholly undefiled, * Mother, who gave birth to life, pure Virgin, * end all scandals which still beset Church, * and as you are loving, Mother, grant her peace.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia2F|text', 'text' : 'It is right indeed * we should magnify the one who grants life, * you, that stretched your hands wide upon the Cross, * broke and smashed the might and power of the foe.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia300|title', 'text' : 'Third Section.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia300|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 3.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia301|text', 'text' : 'Each generation offers, * my Christ, for your entombment * in hymns and songs its praises.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia302|text', 'text' : 'The Noble Joseph takes you * down from the Tree, my Saviour, * and in the tomb he lays you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia303|text', 'text' : 'Myrrh-bearing Woman came then, * providently bringing * to you, O Christ, the sweet myrrh.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia304|text', 'text' : 'Let all Creation join us, * as to the Creator * our farewell hymns we now sing.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia305|text', 'text' : 'With myrrh-bearing women * let us, with understanding, * anoint as dead the Living.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia306|text', 'text' : 'O thrice-blessed Joseph, * entomb Messiah's body, * the corpse of Him who grants life.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia307|text', 'text' : 'Those he fed with manna * raised their heels against him, * against the Benefactor.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia308|text', 'text' : 'Those he fed with manna * bring vinegar and gall now * to offer to the Saviour..'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia309|text', 'text' : 'O the boundless folly * of those who slew the prophets * and now slay God's Anointed.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia310|text', 'text' : 'Initiate yet traitor, * he, the senseless servant, * sold the Abyss of Wisdom.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia311|text', 'text' : 'Judas the deceiver * for silver sold the Saviour, * and thus became a captive.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia312|text', 'text' : 'Solomon declared it: * like a deep-dug pit the mouth * of Law-transgressing Hebrews.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia313|text', 'text' : 'Law-transgressing Hebrews * on the crooked paths they tread * face pits and traps and sharp snares.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia314|text', 'text' : 'With Nicodemus, Joseph * buries the Creator * as for the dead is fitting.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia315|text', 'text' : 'O Life-giving Saviour, * the conqueror of Hades, * to your great might be glory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia316|text', 'text' : 'When the All-Pure saw you * lying limp and dead, Lord, * as mother, Word, she mourned you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia317|text', 'text' : '"O my sweetest springtime, * O my sweetest Offspring, * where has your beauty vanished?"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia318|text', 'text' : 'What sad lament she raises, * O Word, your all-pure Mother, * as you lie dead before her.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia319|text', 'text' : 'Women with sweet myrrh came * to anoint with myrrh Christ, * who is himself Divine Myrrh.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia320|text', 'text' : 'Death itself, O Saviour, * by death you put to death, Lord * my God, by your divine might.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia321|text', 'text' : 'Deceived is the deceiver, * the once deceived redeemed now * my God and by your Wisdom.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia322|text', 'text' : 'Behold the traitor cast down, * to Hades' depths abysmal, * the deep pit of destruction.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia323|text', 'text' : 'Traps and pits and sharp snares - * these are the ways of Judas, * the madman and thrice-wretched.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia324|text', 'text' : 'All those who crucified you * will be destroyed together, * God's Word and Son, the Great King.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia325|text', 'text' : 'All the men of blood now * will be destroyed together * within destruction's deep pit.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia326|text', 'text' : 'Son of God, All-Sovereign, * my God and my Creator, * why did you will to suffer?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia327|text', 'text' : 'The heifer, when she saw him, * her calf, hanged on the dread Tree, * raised up a cry of great grief.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia328|text', 'text' : 'See, noble Joseph buries * the one life-bearing Body, * and Nicodemus helps him.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia329|text', 'text' : 'The weeping Maiden cried out, * and from her eyes hot tears pour, * as to the heart she is pierced.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia330|text', 'text' : '"O Light that gives my eyes light, * my gentle Son, my sweet Child, * why does the tomb now hide you?"'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia331|text', 'text' : '"To free both Eve and Adam, * Mother, this I suffer. * Come, do not grieve and sorrow."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia332|text', 'text' : '"The depth of your compassion, * I glorify my dear Son, * which makes you suffer these things."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia333|text', 'text' : 'They gave you gall to drink, Lord, * and vinegar, Most Loving: * the apple's taste now passes.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia334|text', 'text' : 'To a post they nailed you, * who once your people sheltered * below a cloudy pillar.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia335|text', 'text' : 'Myrrh-bearing women, Saviour, * approach your tomb to bring you * the sweet myrrh to anoint you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia336|text', 'text' : 'Arise, O Lord of mercy, * and from the depths of Hades * now raise us all up with you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia337|text', 'text' : 'Through her tears, your Mother, * who gave you birth now cries out * "Arise, O Giver of life."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia338|text', 'text' : 'Make haste to rise again, Word, * abolish now her grieving, * the all pure Maid, who bore you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia339|text', 'text' : 'Heaven's awesome powers * stood amazed in terror, * to see you lying lifeless.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia340|text', 'text' : 'To those who love and fear you, * and honour your dread Passion, * now give release from all faults.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia341|text', 'text' : 'A dread and most strange sight, this, * O Word of God now tell us, * how can earth cover you, Lord?'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia342|text', 'text' : 'One Joseph bore you, Saviour * with him in flight, a second, * to burial now bears you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia343|text', 'text' : 'Your all-pure Mother, Saviour, * with tears and lamentation * now mourns for you, who lie slain.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia344|text', 'text' : 'All Heaven's angels tremble * Creator of the Cosmos, * at your strange, dread entombment.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia345|text', 'text' : 'Myrrh-bearers came and sprinkled * sweet myrrh upon your tomb, Lord, * at early dawn they come now.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia346|text', 'text' : 'Peace unto your Church, Lord, * salvation to your people, * grant by your Resurrection.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia3TrVerse|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia3Tr|text', 'text' : 'Father, Son and Spirit, * O Trinity, my One God, * have mercy on the whole world.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia3TVerse|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia3T|text', 'text' : 'Count all your servants worthy, * to see, Most Holy Virgin, * you Son's bright Resurrection.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trHW|Encomia3F|text', 'text' : 'Each generation offers, * my Christ, for your entombment * in hymns and songs its praises.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trTE|Troparion|text', 'text' : 'Christ, who hold fast the ends of the earth, you accepted to be held fast in a tomb, that you might ransom humanity from the maw of Hell, * and as immortal God you have given us life and immortality.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d070_en_UK_lash|trTE|Troparion2|text', 'text' : 'And as immortal God you have given us life and immortality.'}
